org.oucs.gaboto.entities.pool
Class GabotoEntityPool

java.lang.Object
  org.oucs.gaboto.entities.pool.GabotoEntityPool

public class GabotoEntityPool
extends java.lang.Object

A collection of GabotoEntitys that for some reason belong together.

An GabotoEntityPool can be seen as a collection of GabotoEntitys that have something in common. GabotoEntityPools can be created by simply adding entities "by hand" or they can be automatically created from an GabotoSnapshot or a Jena Model.

The automatic creation is configured using a GabotoEntityPoolConfiguration object.

Version:
0.1
Author:
Arno Mittelbach
See Also:

filterEntities

public void filterEntities(java.util.Collection<EntityFilter> filters)
Removes entities that do not fulfill all filter criteria.

GabotoEntitys in this pool might still hold references to removed entities after filtering. Filtered entities are only removed from the pool, not from other entities in the pool.

Parameters:
filters - The collection of EntityFilters.

removeEntity

public void removeEntity(GabotoEntity entity)
Removes an entity from this pool.

The entity will only be removed from the pool. Even if any other entity in this pool holds a reference to the deleted entity, that reference will not be deleted.

Parameters:
entity - The entity that is to be deleted.
